<div id="post-338" class="cf post-338 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-uncategorized">

	<h2>
		<span class="post-format"></span>
		<a href="http://werblog.com/2002/11/david-gelernter-an-operating/" title="David Gelernter: &quot;An operating" rel="bookmark">David Gelernter: &quot;An operating</a>
		
	</h2>

	
	
	<div class="post-bodycopy cf">
	
		<div class="post-date">		
			<p class="post-month">Nov</p>
			<p class="post-day">7</p>
			<p class="post-year">2002</p>				
		</div>

		David Gelernter: &quot;An operating system connects the user (and the user&#8217;s software) to the ensemble of machines we call a computer. But nowadays users no longer want to be connected to computers. They want to be connected to information, a claim that sounds vague but is clear and specific.&quot;
		
	</div>

